Suspected murder of the former a senior defunct Baringo County Council clerk Stephen Kiprono was today released on sh300, 000 bond at Kabarnet high court. The accused Betty Jemutai, 40, wife of the deceased, who appeared before the high court judge Edward Muriithi today did not take plea, instead she was granted her freedom to undergo mental assessment on Tuesday 26. “Having found no tangible reason to continue detaining her I therefore release her on bond of the above amount with three sureties of the same” Muriithi said. He reached at the conclusion after the accused said she owns a cosmetic and also works as a salonist in Kabarnet town earning at least sh90,000 per month.  